cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CR 

This paper is about scene labeling, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a dynamic hierarchical model that optimizes the trade-off between efficiency and accuracy, which involves learning a sequence of image-adaptive hierarchical models. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with semantic segmentation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) that involves labeling words or phrases in text with their corresponding semantic categories. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and cryptography and security (cs.CR), which deal with NLP and data privacy, respectively.
